  <summary>1/27/2009--Introduced.
Urges the Secretary of the Treasury to: (1) halt the purchase of a luxury corporate jet by Citigroup or require Citigroup to reimburse the Treasury for its cost; (2) require Troubled Asset Relief Program (TARP) recipients to spend tax dollars to help homeowners, small businesses, and others hurt by the recession; and (3) place further restrictions on TARP recipients to limit executive compensation and other benefits.</summary>
